How To Use Number Functions In PHP!

<?php
$x = 55;
var_dump(is_int($x));

echo "<br>";

$x= 55.55;
var_dump(is_int($x));
?>

This will output true if the number is an interger or false if it is not classified as an interger!
You Can Do The Same Thing, But With Floats!

<?php
$x = 10.365;
var_dump(is_float($x));
?>

If a number is smaller or bigger than an interger or a float then you can call it an infinite!
Use This Function To Check If A Number is finite, or infinite!
<?php
$x = 1.9e411;
var_dump($x);
?>
